text: Reinbek is a town in Stormarn in Schleswig-Holstein, Germany. It is part of the Hamburg Metropolitan Region. Reinbek was first mentioned in 1226 and was given city rights in 1952. == Twin towns == Reinbek is twinned with: * Täby, Sweden, since 1956 * Königslutter, Germany, since 1961 * Padasjoki, Finland, since 1974 * Koło, Poland, since 1999 == References == == Other websites == * Official website Category:Towns in Schleswig-Holstein
title: Reinbek
